                                    "Inputs": [
                                        {
                                            "Type": "Text",
                                            "Parameters": {
                                                "IsHtml": true,
                                                "Text": "<b><font color=\"#9769ED\" size=6>Huntington's Disease Society of America (HDSA)</font></b><br /><br />HDSA provides comprehensive support for individuals and families affected by Huntington\u2019s disease through community services, education, advocacy, and research. <br /><br /><a href=\"https://hdsa.org/\">https://hdsa.org/</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><font color=\"#9769ED\" size=6>HDSA Centers of Excellence</font></b><br /><br />Discover comprehensive care and support for HD at HDSA Centers of Excellence. Professionals in neurology, psychiatry, and more guide families through every stage of HD.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://hdsa.org/find-help/clinical-care-services/hdsa-centers-of-excellence/\">https://hdsa.org/find-help/clinical-care-services/hdsa-centers-of-excellence/</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><font color=\"#9769ED\" size=6>HDSA Helpline</font></b><br /><br />The HDSA Helpline is operated by trained HD social workers. Available Monday \u2013 Friday, 9 a.m. \u2013 5 p.m. EST. For support and guidance tailored to the challenges of HD families, contact the HDSA Helpline at 800-345-HDSA (4372).<br /><br /><a href=\"https://hdsa.org/find-help/community-social-support/\">https://hdsa.org/find-help/community-social-support/</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><font color=\"#9769ED\" size=6>HDSA Telehealth</font></b><br /><br />HDSA's Telehealth Program offers free counseling sessions with licensed social workers and psychologists specializing in HD. Access sessions through www.hdsa.amwell.com or the Amwell\u00ae app using the Service Key HDSA. Each HD family member can schedule up to 8 visits per year.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://hdsa.org/find-help/community-social-support/hdsa-telehealth/\">https://hdsa.org/find-help/community-social-support/hdsa-telehealth/</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><font color=\"#9769ED\" size=6>HDSA's Locate Resources Tool</font></b><br /><br />Find help by clicking on 1 or more selection(s) to find services and providers in your area. Options include physicians, physical therapists, legal resources, speech therapists, and more.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://hdsa.org/about-hdsa/locate-resources/\">https://hdsa.org/about-hdsa/locate-resources/</a><br /><br /><br /><br />"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "CanBeFavorited": true
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "Name": "Youth & Young Adult",
                            "Title": "Youth & Young Adult",
                            "Type": "Survey",
                            "Pages": [
                                {
                                    "Conditions": [
                                        {
